100:00:02,486 --> 00:00:05,539Welcome to the Stealth beginner tutorial project.200:00:07,351 --> 00:00:09,709In Stealth you play the role of Ethan,300:00:09,709 --> 00:00:11,709a teenager who has stumbled across the400:00:11,709 --> 00:00:13,855simulation zone of Unity Labs whilst on a500:00:13,855 --> 00:00:15,855tour of the facility.600:00:16,659 --> 00:00:18,659Finding yourself in the midst of a hostile700:00:18,659 --> 00:00:21,172environment, you must sneak around, avoid the800:00:21,172 --> 00:00:23,661guards and security cameras, unlock laser900:00:23,661 --> 00:00:27,208gates and find the key card to escape the simulation.1000:00:28,109 --> 00:00:30,109During the four chapters of this project1100:00:30,109 --> 00:00:33,477you will learn: how to set up game systems,1200:00:33,477 --> 00:00:36,200and create a player responsive alarm in the environment,1300:00:37,805 --> 00:00:39,805how to build a player character with1400:00:39,805 --> 00:00:41,805various animations and interactions,1500:00:44,294 --> 00:00:46,789how to setup dynamic elements of the environment,1600:00:46,789 --> 00:00:50,024such as doors, the key and the lift,1700:00:53,038 --> 00:00:55,038and how to create AI enemies with a1800:00:55,038 --> 00:00:57,038simple state machine.1900:00:59,871 --> 00:01:01,968If you'd like to try out the game you can2000:01:01,968 --> 00:01:03,760play it online on the project page.2100:01:04,302 --> 00:01:06,302or simply open the completed scene2200:01:06,302 --> 00:01:08,123in the Done Scenes folder of your 2300:01:08,123 --> 00:01:10,123downloaded project.